---
import Layout from "../../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../../../css/services.css";
---

<Layout
  title="Custom Software Development | GeneralSoft UAE"
  description="Expert custom software development services in the UAE. We build scalable, secure, and high-performance enterprise applications."
  path="/services/custom-software/"
  image="/img/og-custom-software.jpg"
>
  <section class="service-content" id="software-services">
    <div class="service-section" style="margin-top: 120px;">
      <h2 class="service-title">Custom Software Development</h2>
      <p>
        Off-the-shelf software rarely fits the unique workflows, compliance
        requirements, and growth trajectories of businesses operating in the
        UAE's dynamic economy. At GeneralSoft, we build custom software
        solutions that align precisely with your operational reality — whether
        you need an enterprise ERP, a specialized line-of-business application,
        or a complex integration layer connecting multiple systems.
      </p>
      <p>
        Our development approach is grounded in three decades of hands-on
        engineering experience across finance, healthcare, logistics,
        manufacturing, and government sectors. We don't just write code — we
        design systems that are maintainable, scalable, and built to evolve with
        your business.
      </p>

      <h3>Our Development Capabilities</h3>
      <div class="features-grid">
        <div class="feature-box">
          <h4>Enterprise Applications</h4>
          <p>
            Full-stack enterprise applications using .NET 6/8, Java (Jakarta
            EE), and modern frameworks with clean architecture principles.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-box">
          <h4>ERP & Business Systems</h4>
          <p>
            Custom ERP solutions and integration with SAP S/4HANA, Microsoft
            Dynamics 365, and Oracle Fusion Cloud.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-box">
          <h4>API & Integration Layer</h4>
          <p>
            RESTful APIs, gRPC, GraphQL, and enterprise integration patterns
            using Azure Integration Services and BizTalk.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-box">
          <h4>Cloud-Native Development</h4>
          <p>
            Cloud-native applications on Azure, AWS, and GCP with
            microservices, containers, and serverless architecture.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Projects Proof Section -->
      <div class="projects-proof">
        <h3>Proven Delivery — Projects Completed</h3>
        <p>
          Our portfolio spans three decades of custom software delivery across
          industries and geographies. Here are representative projects that
          demonstrate our engineering depth.
        </p>

        <div class="project-card">
          <h4>ERP Solution for Elahi Electronics</h4>
          <div class="project-meta">
            <span class="date">Jun 2009 – Nov 2010</span>
            <span class="role">Architect & Lead Developer</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            Designed and implemented a complete Small & Medium Enterprise (SME)
            ERP solution covering authentication, authorization, and
            role-based access in SharePoint using FBA. Built a rich interface
            application in Silverlight with WCF RIA Services as the ERP client.
            Developed business intelligence using SQL Server Analysis Services
            (SSAS) and ETL pipelines using SSIS. Integrated enterprise search
            with FAST Search for SharePoint (FS4SP) with multilingual word
            translation capabilities.
          </p>
          <div class="tech-tags">
            <span class="tech-tag">C#</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">SQL Server 2008 R2</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">SSIS</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">SSAS</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">SharePoint</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">WCF RIA</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">BizTalk 2009</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="project-card">
          <h4>Loan Workflow Application — Major Bank</h4>
          <div class="project-meta">
            <span class="date">Jan 2006 – Sep 2006</span>
            <span class="role">Architect & Lead Developer</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            Developed proof-of-concept loan workflow applications for a large
            bank, integrating Windows Server 2003, WSS, BizTalk 2006, and
            Fuego. Built custom controls for hosting Microsoft Office documents
            inside a browser for seamless integration with BEA's WebLogic
            Portal. The solution automated loan origination, document
            management, and approval workflows.
          </p>
          <div class="tech-tags">
            <span class="tech-tag">BizTalk 2006</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">SharePoint</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">InfoPath</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">WebLogic</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">Workflow</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="project-card">
          <h4>Enterprise Content Management — Hospitality</h4>
          <div class="project-meta">
            <span class="date">Jun 2007 – Aug 2007</span>
            <span class="role">Architect & Lead Developer</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            Created a corporate ECM system for 22,000+ employees in the
            hospitality industry. Used extensive BizTalk reflection to reverse
            engineer documentation for the ECM. Authored a 390-page training
            manual for the system. The solution managed enterprise-wide content
            lifecycle, compliance documentation, and knowledge management.
          </p>
          <div class="tech-tags">
            <span class="tech-tag">SharePoint 2007 ECM</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">C#</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">.NET 3.5</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">BizTalk</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="project-card">
          <h4>App For Hygiene Service Providers</h4>
          <div class="project-meta">
            <span class="date">Sep 2021 – Dec 2022</span>
            <span class="role">Media Consultant & Trainer. Web & App Developer.</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            Developed a cross-platform mobile application for hygiene service
            providers in Abu Dhabi. Built with Flutter and a microservices
            backend architecture. The app manages service scheduling, customer
            management, and real-time service tracking.
          </p>
          <div class="tech-tags">
            <span class="tech-tag">Flutter</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">Microservices</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">Mobile</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">Firebase</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3>Technology Stack</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Backend:</strong> .NET 6/8, Java (Jakarta EE), C#, F#, Python</li>
        <li><strong>Frontend:</strong> Angular, Bootstrap, WPF, XAML</li>
        <li><strong>Databases:</strong> SQL Server 2019/2022, Oracle 19c/21c, Azure Cosmos DB</li>
        <li><strong>Cloud:</strong> Microsoft Azure, AWS, Google Cloud Platform</li>
        <li><strong>Integration:</strong> Azure Logic Apps, BizTalk, MQSeries, REST APIs</li>
        <li><strong>DevOps:</strong> Azure DevOps, Git, Octopus Deploy, Docker, Kubernetes</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Our Development Process</h3>
      <p>
        We follow a structured, transparent development methodology that keeps
        you informed at every stage:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Discovery & Requirements:</strong> Deep-dive sessions to understand your business processes, pain points, and goals</li>
        <li><strong>Architecture & Design:</strong> Solution architecture with clear documentation and technology selection rationale</li>
        <li><strong>Iterative Development:</strong> Agile sprints with regular demos and feedback loops</li>
        <li><strong>Quality Assurance:</strong> Automated testing, code reviews, and performance benchmarking</li>
        <li><strong>Deployment & Support:</strong> Managed deployment with ongoing maintenance and enhancement options</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="faq-container">
        <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
          Common questions about our custom software development process in the UAE.
        </p>

        <div class="faq-list">
          <details>
            <summary>How long does it take to build a custom software application?</summary>
            <p>
              Timelines vary based on complexity. A focused line-of-business
              application typically takes 8–16 weeks from requirements to
              deployment. Enterprise-scale systems with multiple integrations
              generally require 4–8 months. We provide a detailed project
              timeline after the discovery phase.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Do you integrate with existing systems like SAP or Dynamics 365?</summary>
            <p>
              Yes. We have extensive experience integrating with SAP S/4HANA
              (SD, FI, CO, MM, HR), Microsoft Dynamics 365 (Finance, Supply
              Chain, CRM), and Oracle Fusion Cloud. Our integration layer
              expertise includes BizTalk, Azure Logic Apps, MQSeries, and
              custom API development.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>What industries do you serve in the UAE?</summary>
            <p>
              We serve healthcare, financial services, logistics, retail,
              manufacturing, hospitality, and government sectors. Our team has
              deep domain knowledge in each of these industries, including
              relevant regulatory and compliance requirements.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Do you provide ongoing maintenance after deployment?</summary>
            <p>
              Absolutely. We offer flexible maintenance and support packages
              that include bug fixes, performance monitoring, security patches,
              and feature enhancements. Many of our clients continue working
              with us long after the initial deployment.
            </p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="contact" id="contact">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="contact-content">
        <h2>Let's Build Something Great Together</h2>
        <p>
          Ready to transform your business with custom software solutions?
          Get in touch with our team today.
        </p>
        <div class="contact-info">
          <div class="contact-item">
            <div class="contact-item-icon">🌐</div><strong>Website</strong><a
              href="https://generalsoft.ae">generalsoft.ae</a
            >
          </div>
          <div class="contact-item">
            <a href="/contact/"
              ><div class="contact-item-icon">📧</div><strong>Contact Us</strong
              ><br />Get in touch</a
            >
          </div>
          <div class="contact-item">
            <div class="contact-item-icon">📍</div><strong>Location</strong
            ><span>Ras Al Khaimah</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
